stylometry: Safety stock concept is obtaining backup inventory to benefit lead time between when an order is placed and received using a variety of variables. It is important in a company to allow safety stock because of the fact that demand in unknown; which is this biggest issue in the topics we discuss. Everything is correlated around demand. Safety stock allows a company to reduce risk of losing money for having an over abundance of stock that won't be sold. Inventory costs are essentiall also - because high inventory means high holding costs, but demand is met - low inventory may have the low holding costs but demand may not be met and safety stock helps the balance for a company and ensures that inventory is minimized but won't run out.
